---
import AudioPlayer from "../../components/AudioPlayer";
import TeacherMessage from "../../components/TeacherMessage";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  return [{ params: { exercice: "z" } }];
}
---

<Layout
  title="Letra Z"
  description="Explicación de cómo suena la letra Z en inglés y en español "
>
  <article class="flex flex-col justify-center">
    <section class="-mb-6 sm:mb-12 mt-20 sm:mt-48">
      <div
        class="flex items-center w-[90%] sm:w-[80%] mx-auto transform justify-center"
      >
        <img
          src="/images/svg/z/Fonema_Z.svg"
          alt="Fonema Z"
          class="w-4/12 sm:w-3/12 transform sm:translate-x-24"
        />
        <div
          class="flex items-center ml-4 sm:ml-48 max-w-[50%] sm:max-w-[100%] transform translate-x-8 sm:translate-x-0"
        >
          <p class="text-xl sm:text-5xl max-w-[100%] sm:max-w-[100%]">
            La <span class="text-bold text-[#6610F2]">letra z</span> se pronuncia
            siempre como la letra s en castellano.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20">
      <div class="flex justify-center max-w-[95%] sm:max-w-[50%] mx-auto">
        <p class="text-lg sm:text-2xl text-center mb-12">
          Es decir, siempre pronunciamos como la <span class="text-bold"
            >letra <span class="text-[#6610F2]">s</span></span
          > las palabras escritas con las
          <span class="text-bold"
            >letras <span class="text-[#6610F2]">s</span> y <span class="text-[#6610F2]">z</span>.</span
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <div
        class="flex justify-center max-w-[90%] sm:max-w-[70%] mx-auto -mb-8 sm:mb-12"
      >
        <p class="text-lg sm:text-3xl text-center">
          Pensemos <span class="text-bold">por ejemplo</span> en la pronunciación
          de:
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:gap-x-48 mt-10">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
            <img
              src="/images/png/z/Zona.png"
              alt="Zona"
              class="h-full max-w-[70%] sm:max-w-[100%] sm:mb-2"
            />
            <p
              class="text-[#6610F2] text-4xl sm:text-6xl text-extrabold sm:mb-6"
            >
              Zona
            </p>
            <AudioPlayer
              audio_path={"/audio/z/Zona.mp3"}
              className="w-24 h-24 sm:w-20 sm:h-20"
              client:load
            />
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
            <img
              src="/images/png/z/Sana.png"
              alt="Sana"
              class="h-full max-w-[70%] xl:max-w-[100%] sm:mb-2"
            />
            <p
              class="text-[#6610F2] text-4xl sm:text-6xl text-extrabold sm:mb-6"
            >
              Sana
            </p>
            <AudioPlayer
              audio_path={"/audio/z/Sana.mp3"}
              className="w-24 h-24 sm:w-20 sm:h-20"
              client:load
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <!-- Seccion de "En ingles" -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div
        class="flex flex-col justify-center max-w-[90%] sm:max-w-[100%] mx-auto"
      >
        <p
          class="text-lg sm:text-2xl max-w-[90%] sm:max-w-[40%] text-center mb-28 sm:mb-10 mx-auto"
        >
          Tal como lo puedes notar, cuando pronunciamos las <span
            class="text-bold"
            >letras <span class="text-[#6610F2]">s</span> y <span
              class="text-[#6610F2]">z</span
            >
          </span>, no hacemos <span class="text-bold"
            >ninguna diferencia entre ambas.</span
          >
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        class="sm:grid sm:grid-cols-12 gap-[15px] flex justify-center w-[85%] sm:w-[75%] mx-auto -mb-20 sm:-mb-28"
      >
        <img
          src="/images/svg/global/Mano_Derecha.svg"
          alt="Imagen de una mano apuntando a la derecha"
          class="w-36 col-start-1 col-span-5 transform -translate-y-24"
        />
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col justify-center max-w-[90%] sm:max-w-[100%] mx-auto mb-12"
      >
        <p
          class="text-lg sm:text-2xl max-w-[90%] text-center sm:max-w-[40%] mx-auto"
        >
          De hecho, bien podriamos escribir <span class="text-bold">
            <span class="text-[#6610F2]">s</span> o <span class="text-[#6610F2]"
              >z</span
            >, pero las pronunciamos igual:
          </span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto -mb-12 sm:mb-0">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:gap-x-48">
          <div class="flex flex-col text-center justify-center items-center">
            <p
              class="text-extrabold text-4xl sm:text-6xl sm:mb-2 sm:leading-[79.36px]"
            >
              <span class="text-[#6610F2]">S</span>ona
            </p>
            <AudioPlayer
              audio_path={"/audio/z/Zona.mp3"}
              className="w-24 h-24 sm:w-20 sm:h-20"
              client:load
            />
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col text-center justify-center items-center">
            <p
              class="text-extrabold text-4xl sm:text-6xl sm:mb-2 sm:leading-[79.36px]"
            >
              <span class="text-[#6610F2]">Z</span>ana
            </p>
            <AudioPlayer
              audio_path={"/audio/z/Sana.mp3"}
              className="w-24 h-24 sm:w-20 sm:h-20"
              client:load
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col justify-center max-w-[90%] sm:max-w-[100%] mx-auto"
      >
        <p
          class="text-lg sm:text-2xl text-center mt-20 sm:mb-10 mx-auto sm:max-w-[48%]"
        >
          Aunque sabríamos que la <span class="text-bold"
            >ortografía no es la correcta</span
          >, en nuestras mentes seguiríamos pensando en una <span
            class="text-bold text-[#6610F2]">zona</span
          > geográfica y en una persona <span class="text-bold text-[#6610F2]"
            >sana</span
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="-mb-40 sm:-mb-56">
      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-12 grid-rows-2 gap-[15px] w-[90%] sm:w-[75%] mx-auto"
      >
        <div
          class="col-end-13 col-span-12 c500:col-end-13 c500:col-span-7 sm:max-w-[90%] ml-auto sm:col-end-13 sm:col-span-9 lg:col-end-13 lg:col-span-7"
        >
          <p class="text-lg sm:text-2xl text-right leading-[1.45rem]">
            En inglés, las <span class="text-bold">letras</span>
            <span class="text-bold"><span class="text-[#6610F2]">s</span> y</span>
            <span class="text-bold text-[#6610F2]">z</span> al inicio de una
            <span class="inline xs:inline c400:block c500:inline"
              >palabra tiene <span class="text-bold"
                >pronunciaciones distintas y</span
              ></span
            >
            <span class="inline xs:inline c400:block c500:inline"
              ><span class="text-bold">significados distintos.</span></span
            >
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="col-start-1 col-span-5 sm:col-start-1 sm:col-span-4 transform -translate-y-44 c400:-translate-y-44 c500:-translate-y-56
